The paper deals with a communication scenario where multiple users send information to a single receiver over a common channel, and the focus is on optimizing the throughput of the system. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of Markov chains to model the fading process of each user suggests a connection to stochastic processes and control (cs.SY), while the consideration of a successive interference decoder indicates a possible link to networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the use of game-theoretic concepts to analyze the behavior of selfish users in a shared communication channel suggests a connection to multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
